For Singapore Office:
 Translates all documents, worksheets, and reports from one language to another (English to Chinese and vis versa).
 Interprets at meetings.
 Supports to prepare and consolidate documents, reports, and data analysis.
 Maintain IT-related licenses and provide office-level ad hoc IT coordination.
 To verify and arrange monthly payments such as seasonal parking, IT vendor.
 Coordinates and arrange meeting logistics, support the organization of employee activities, visitor reception, and management meeting document binding support.
 Manage the telephone switchboard.
 Application and Submission of a Singapore Visa.
 Support the Head of Singapore Office with the government officially visit arrangement, townhall organization etc.
Finance
 Data entries for vendors invoices, staff claims and payment vouchers
 Process payment within credit terms of Supplier/Vendor
 Monthly billing for payment on behalf
 Photocopying and filling all invoices and source documents
 Prepare bank reconciliations
 Prepare balance sheet schedules
 Prepare journal entries
 Timely update of cash book and monitor cashflow
 Assist with new modules set-up in new system database in ERP accounting system
 Handle ad-hoc duties as assigned by the management